    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```typescript\ntest('User Login and Profile Load Stability Test', async ({ page }) => {\n  await page.goto('/login');\n  await page.fill('#username', 'testuser');\n  await page.fill('#password', 'password123');\n  await page.click('#loginButton');\n\n  // Explicitly wait for the dashboard element to confirm successful navigation, not just the network request.\n  await page.waitForSelector('#dashboard-container', { state: 'visible' });\n\n  // Robustly wait for the profile data API call to complete before asserting.\n  await page.waitForResponse(response => \n    response.url().includes('/api/user/profile') && response.status() === 200\n  );\n\n  // Assertions are now based on the guaranteed presence of data after the wait.\n  await expect(page.locator('#user-name')).toHaveText('Test User');\n  await expect(page.locator('#last-login')).toContainText('2024-01-01');\n});\n```\nThis code forces the test to wait until the specific profile API call returns a 200 status",
